article.description: Sha Brooks scored 25 points and Marshae Dotson made all eight shots from the field for 19 points to lead Florida over South Carolina 77-63.
article.headline: Brooks, Dotson help Gators beat Gamecocks
article.linkText: Brooks, Dotson lift Florida past South Carolina
article.story:
COLUMBIA, S.C. -- Sha Brooks scored 25 points and Marshae Dotson made all eight shots from the field for 19 points, to lead No. 19 Florida over South Carolina 77-63 on Thursday night.

The Gators (16-2, 2-1 Southeastern Conference) are off to their best start since 2000-01 and bounced back after having their school-record 15-game winning streak snapped by Auburn (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 6 AP).

Florida shot 45.8 percent (27-fo-59) from the field and forced 24 turnovers. The Gators have shot better than 40 percent in all but one game this season.

Brionna Dickerson had 20 points and seven rebounds, while Demetress Adams added 10 points and nine rebounds for South Carolina (8-8, 0-3).

The Gators trailed 16-13 with just over nine minutes to go in the first half, but finished with a 22-9 run, thanks to its pressing defense. South Carolina made just four of its last 13 shots in the half, and turned the ball over eight times in the final nine minutes of the half.

Florida slowly stretched its lead out over the second half, at one point scoring on seven straight possessions to take a 65-44 lead with just under eight minutes to go. Brooks, who tied a school record starting in her 109th consecutive game, scored eight points during the run.

South Carolina fought back, cutting the Gators lead to 68-59 with 54.8 seconds to go, thanks to Florida's sloppy play and missed free throws.

The Gators are trying to make it back to the NCAA tournament. They had a string of nine NCAAs in 10 years from 1993 to 2002 but have made it to the tournament just twice in the past six years.

South Carolina hasn't beaten a ranked SEC opponent in nearly six years. The Gamecocks get another chance Sunday against Tennessee (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP), but they have beaten the Lady Vols just once in 38 tries, back in 1980.
